A cozy living room in Studio Ghibli style, warm afternoon light streaming through large windows, where two young children sit on a soft rug playing with wooden blocks and picture books, their backs to an old television set that's been unplugged and pushed into a dusty corner, covered partially by a knitted blanket. Houseplants overflow from the windowsill, and a gentle breeze moves sheer curtains. The children are animated and engaged, one pointing excitedly at a colorful illustration. Soft watercolor textures, dreamy atmospheric lighting, gentle earth tones with pops of cheerful yellow and green, capturing a sense of peaceful domestic simplicity and childhood wonder reclaimed.
